        classOfRec: "I",
        classNote: null,
        levelOfEvidence: "C-EO",
        text: "Facilities caring for acute stroke patients that do not provide 24/7 thrombectomy (e.g., ASRH, PSC) are recommended to develop interfacility transfer protocols for fast, safe, and efficient transfer of potentially EVT-eligible patients.",
