        section: "Stroke Registries, Quality Improvement, and",
        classOfRec: "I",
        classNote: null,
        levelOfEvidence: "B-R",
        text: "Facilities treating acute stroke patients are recommended to engage in multicomponent quality improvement processes involving continuous monitoring, review, and feedback of stroke quality indicators and evidence-based practices to increase care quality, improve outcomes, and reduce health care disparities.",
